<p>I got the following charset: <code>+ /</code>, <code>0-9</code>, <code>A-Z</code>, <code>a-z</code>. The data is hashed with the sha256 algorithm. The given charset (base64) is used with a fixed length of 64.</p>  <p>Example plain text:<br> <code>AJJfxak21MrBQ3N3W78Gdiwd8M57IL9v8GeWPZhXLocIdFFvrRUkxc1a5n6ysBlm</code><br> And the corresponding sha256 hash: <code>61c8f777da1a8048e765abd62c26c859f762fddb2de5054f005288c3d22662bf</code></p>  <p>How can I calculate the estimated duration of the bruteforce?</p>